{{nihongo|'''Shinj<U+014D>'''|<U+65B0><U+5E84><U+5E02>|Shinj<U+014D>-shi}} is a [[Cities of Japan|city]] in [[Yamagata Prefecture]], Japan.

As of October 2013, the city had an estimated [[population]] of 37,637 and a [[population density]] of 169 persons per km<U+00B2>. The total area was 223.08 km<U+00B2>. 

==Geography==
Shinj<U+014D> is located in a mountain basin in north-central Yamagata Prefecture. The [[Mogami River]] runs through the city. 

